    <p>The pattern is clear: for nutrients requiring small to moderate doses — which includes most vitamins, adaptogens, and herbal extracts — gummies are clinically equivalent. The limitations appear exclusively with nutrients requiring large physical doses or those incompatible with the gummy matrix chemistry. This data supports a practical hybrid approach that many informed consumers already use: gummies for daily vitamins and adaptogens, pills for high-dose minerals and omega-3s.</p>

