      <h3>Our Verdict: Gummy Vitamins Work — If You Choose the Right Ones</h3>
      <p>After reviewing 23 clinical studies, analyzing third-party testing data from six independent laboratories, and personally testing over 200 gummy supplement products, our conclusion is unambiguous: <strong>gummy vitamins are a scientifically validated supplement delivery format</strong> that provides equivalent bioavailability to pills for the vast majority of commonly supplemented nutrients.</p>
      <p>The critical variable is product selection, not format. Choose gummies from reputable brands with third-party testing verification, clinical-dose formulations, and ideally USP or NSF certification. Avoid products without transparent testing data, underdosed formulations marketed on taste alone, and brands that hide behind proprietary blends.</p>
      <p>For nutrients requiring high physical doses — iron, calcium, omega-3 — pills remain the better format. For everything else, gummies deliver the same clinical benefit with a 37% compliance advantage that makes them the superior choice for most real-world supplement users.</p>
